title: This Week’s Games
text:
Lancaster (5-0) at Groveport (4-1) 
• In 2014: The Golden Gales were 7-3; The Cruisers were 2-8. 
• Last meeting: Lancaster won 35-0 in 2014. 
• Radio: WLOH (104.5-FM). 
• Of note: Lancaster continues to be solid on both sides of the ball and had another outstanding performance last week in its win at Pickerington North. The Gales moved from No. 10 to No. 5 in the Division I state Associated Press poll, and stayed at No. 1 in computer poll. The Cruisers will be another tough road test. 
Circleville (4-1) at Bloom-Carroll (3-2) 
• In 2014: The Bulldogs were 4-6; the Tigers were 6-4. 
• Last meeting: Circleville won 36-39 in 2014. 
• Of note: This will be a tough task for the Bulldogs, who need a win to stay in the Mid-State League-Buckeye Division race, as well as the playoff chase. Playing at home on Thursday night should give the Bulldogs a boost. 
Amanda-Clearcreek (1-4) at Fairfield Union (2-3) 
• In 2014: The Aces were 6-5; the Falcons were 2-8. 
• Last meeting: Amanda-Clearcreek won 29-8 in 2014. 
• Radio: WFCO 90.9-FM, digital delay. 
• Of note: Both of these teams have struggled, so something has to give in this game. 
Berne Union (2-3) at Fairfield Christian (1-4) 
• In 2014: The Rockets were 1-9; the Knights were 1-9. 
• Last meeting: Berne Union won 41-19 in 2014. 
• Of note: The Rockets have shown the ability to score a lot of points, and proved last week they could play defense. This could be a high-scoring affair. 
Liberty Union (1-4) at Logan Elm (4-1) 
• In 2014: The Lions were 7-4; the Braves were 7-4. 
• Last meeting: Liberty Union won 22-0 in 2014. 
• Of note: This is a Mid-State League matchup of two teams going in opposite directions. 
Fisher Catholic (3-2) at Grove City Christian (0-5) 
• In 2014: The Irish were 3-7; the Eagles were 6-4. 
• Last meeting: Grove City Christian won 41-37 in 2014. 
• Radio: WLOH (104.5-FM), delayed game. 
• Of note: After losing their first two games, the Irish have won three straight and have put themselves at the top of the Mid-State League-Cardinal Division race, as well as playoff contention. 
Harvest Prep (2-3) at Millersport (2-3) 
• In 2014: The Lakers were 7-3; the Warriors were 8-3. 
• Last meeting: Harvest Prep won 39-0 in 2014. 
• Of note: The injury bug has hit the Lakers, and after a rough start, Harvest Prep seems to be finding its groove. 
Hilliard Bradley (5-0) at Canal Winchester (0-5) 
• In 2014: The Indians were 1-9; the Panthers were 9-2. 
• Last meeting: Hilliard Bradley won 42-7 in 2014. 
• Of note: The Indians continue to show some spark on offense, especially in the second half of games. They will need to get off to a good start against a very good Bradley team. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1KMlPdj More Stories
